message.text:
花火（はなび、Hanabi、Fireworks)の季節がやって来た！
Summer is here　＆ it's the season of Festivals and Big Firework Shows in Japan !

QUESTION:Have you heard of people shouting "Tamaya（たまや、玉屋）" and "Kagiya（かぎや、鍵屋）" during fireworks display?

These are the family names of two famous fireworks factories which played a major role in its development in Japan during Edo period, approx. 200 years ago. As a result of rivalry between two, there was annual fireworks battles, and people supported the favorite factory by yelling their names. Even today, the tradition continues and names are used to express their excitement to see great fireworks display!

There is HUGE fireworks display in Tokyo this week, so why don't you come and try "Tamayaaaaa"?

花火大会で聞く「玉屋」「鍵屋」の掛け声、由来を知っていますか？
江戸時代にライバルだった2つの花火屋さんの名前で、毎年花火の技を競ったときに、アピールや応援のために名前を叫んでいたようです！今年の夏は「玉屋～～～」の掛け声、試してみませんか？

FYI:Light Up Nippon
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FDB1znvWf6E

message.text:
#Hiragana Master
Say it Together! Basic Japanese Words in Japanese Alphabetical Order
Today's Word is "Tsu" TSURU (crane)　#nihongo　
日本の単語を五十音順にわかりやすく紹介！「つ」る

In Japan, Tsuru (crane) is considered as a symbol of good fortune and longevity because of its fabled life span of a thousand years.
This is why we often create "千羽鶴(せんばづる, a thousand origami paper cranes)" to make a wish come true especially during school days or to hope someone's quick recovery from illness. 
Do you know how to make Origami Paper Tsuru? 

「つる」は長寿や幸運のシンボルで、縁起物として考えられているため、日本では折り紙のつるを千羽折る、「千羽鶴」に願いをこめる風習があります。
あなたはつるの折り方、知っていますか？
http://www.origami-fun.com/origami-crane.html

message.text:
Another unique national holiday in Japan is here to come! 
The 3rd Monday of July is MARINE DAY (海の日, Umi no Hi). 
Did you know that Japan is structured by as many as 5 main islands and approximately 6,850 isolated islands? 
Not surprisingly, we are surrounded by a huge body of water! 
This is the day to thank the importance and blessings of mother ocean. 
Many people take advantage of this consecutive three-days off and enjoy fun summer activities. 

What's your plan for the weekend? :)
